A023001.name: a(n) = (8^n - 1)/7.
formula: Also sum of cubes of divisors of 2^(n-1): a(n) = A001158(A000079(n-1)). - _Labos Elemer_, Apr 10 2003 and _Farideh Firoozbakht_, Jun 13 2003

A023002.name: Sum of 10th powers.

G.f.: x*(x - 1)/2 + (1/2)*Sum_{k>=1} mu(k)*x^k/(1 - x^k)^2. - _Ilya Gutkovskiy_, Apr 13 2017

A023023.name: Number of partitions of n into 3 unordered relatively prime parts.
formula: G.f. for the number of partitions of n into m unordered relatively prime parts is Sum(moebius(k)*x^(m*k)/Product(1-x^(i*k), i=1..m), k=1..infinity). - _Vladeta Jovovic_, Dec 21 2004
a(n) = (n^2/12)*Product_{prime p|n} (1 - 1/p^2) for n > 3 (proved by Mohamed El Bachraoui). [_Jonathan Sondow_, May 27 2009]
a(n) = Sum_{k=1..floor(n/3)} Sum_{i=k..floor((n-k)/2)} floor(1/gcd(i,k,n-i-k)). - _Wesley Ivan Hurt_, Jan 02 2021

A023024.name: Number of partitions of n into 4 unordered relatively prime parts.

A023038.name: a(n) = 12*a(n-1) - a(n-2).
formula: a(n) = T(n, 6) = (S(n, 12)-S(n-2, 12))/2 with S(n, x) := U(n, x/2) and T(n), resp. U(n, x), are Chebyshev's polynomials of the first, resp. second, kind. See A053120 and A049310. S(-2, x) := -1, S(-1, x) := 0, S(n, 12)=A004191(n).

A023039.name: a(n) = 18*a(n-1) - a(n-2).

a(n) = T(n, 9) = (S(n, 18)-S(n-2, 18))/2, with S(n, x) := U(n, x/2) and T(n, x), resp. U(n, x), are Chebyshev's polynomials of the first, resp. second, kind. See A053120 and A049310. S(-2, x) := -1, S(-1, x) := 0, S(n, 18)=A049660(n+1).

A023887.name: a(n) = sigma_n(n): sum of n-th powers of divisors of n.
formula: If the canonical prime factorization of n > 1 is the product of p^e(p) then sigma_n(n) = Product_p ((p^(n*(e(p)+1)))-1)/(p^n-1). - Nick Hobson, Nov 25 2006
sigma_n(n) is odd if and only if n is a square or twice a square. - Nick Hobson, Nov 25 2006
Conjecture: sigma_m(n) = sigma(n^m * rad(n)^(m-1))/sigma(rad(n)^(m-1)) for n > 0 and m > 0, where sigma = A000203 and rad = A007947. - _Velin Yanev_, Aug 24 2017

A023888.name: Sum of prime power divisors of n (1 included).
formula: a(1) = 1, a(p) = p+1, a(pq) = p+q+1, a(pq...z) = (p+q+...+z) + 1, a(p^k) = (p^(k+1)-1) / (p-1), for p, q = primes, k = natural numbers, pq...z = product of k (k > 2) distinct primes p, q, ..., z.
G.f.: x/(1 - x) + Sum_{k>=2} floor(1/omega(k))*k*x^k/(1 - x^k), where omega(k) is the number of distinct prime factors (A001221). - _Ilya Gutkovskiy_, Jan 04 2017

A023889.name: Sum of the prime power divisors of n (not including 1).
formula: G.f.: Sum_{k>=2} floor(1/omega(k))*k*x^k/(1 - x^k), where omega(k) is the number of distinct prime factors (A001221). - _Ilya Gutkovskiy_, Jan 04 2017
a(n) = Sum_{d|n} d * [omega(d) = 1], where omega is the number of distinct prime factors and [ ] is the Iverson bracket. - _Wesley Ivan Hurt_, Jan 28 2021

A023890.name: Sum of the nonprime divisors of n.
formula: Equals A051731 * A037282. - _Gary W. Adamson_, Nov 06 2007
a(n) = A023891(n) + 1 (sum of composite divisors of n + 1). [_Alonso del Arte_, Oct 01 2008]
L.g.f.: log(Product_{ k>0 } (1-x^prime(k))/(1-x^k)) = Sum_{ n>0 } (a(n)/n)*x^n. - _Benedict W. J. Irwin_, Jul 05 2016
a(n) = Sum_{d|n} d * (1 - [Omega(d) = 1]), where Omega is the number of prime factors with multiplicity (A001222) and [ ] is the Iverson bracket. - _Wesley Ivan Hurt_, Jan 28 2021

A023891.name: Sum of composite divisors of n.

A023896.name: Sum of positive integers in smallest positive reduced residue system modulo n. a(1) = 1 by convention.
formula: a(n) = phi(n^2)/2 = n*phi(n)/2 = A002618(n)/2 if n>1, a(1)=1. See the Apostol reference for this exercise.
a(n) = Sum_{1 <= k < n, gcd(k, n) = 1} k.
If n = p is a prime, a(p) = T(p-1) where T(k) is the k-th triangular number (A000217). - _Robert G. Wilson v_, Jul 31 2004
If m,n > 1 and gcd(m,n)=1 then a(m*n) = 2*a(m)*a(n). - _Thomas Ordowski_, Nov 09 2014
G.f.: Sum_{n>=1} mu(n)*n*x^n/(1-x^n)^3, where mu(n)=A008683(n). - _Mamuka Jibladze_, Apr 24 2015
G.f. A(x) satisfies A(x) = x/(1 - x)^3 - Sum_{k>=2} k * A(x^k). - _Ilya Gutkovskiy_, Sep 06 2019

A023898.name: Divisor balance of n is an integer.
formula: Divisor balance of n = sum_{d divides n} {d / phi(d)} where phi is Euler's phi function.

A023899.name: Integer values of Divisor balance.
formula: Divisor balance of n = sum_{d divides n} {d / phi(d)} where phi is Euler's phi function.

A023900.name: Dirichlet inverse of Euler totient function (A000010).
formula: a(n) = Sum_{ d divides n } d*mu(d) = Product_{p|n} (1-p).
a(n+1) = det(n+1)/det(n) where det(n) is the determinant of the n X n matrix M_(i, j) = i/gcd(i, j) = lcm(i, j)/j. - _Benoit Cloitre_, Aug 19 2003

a(n) = phi(n)*moebius(A007947(n))*A007947(n)/n. Logarithmic g.f.: Sum_{n >= 1} a(n)*x^n/n = log(F(x)) where F(x) is the g.f. of A117209 and satisfies: 1/(1-x) = Product_{n >= 1} F(x^n). - _Paul D. Hanna_, Mar 03 2006
G.f.: A(x) = Sum_{k >= 1} mu(k) k x^k/(1 - x^k) where mu(k) is the Moebius (Mobius) function, A008683. - _Stuart Clary_, Apr 15 2006
G.f.: A(x) is x times the logarithmic derivative of A117209(x). - _Stuart Clary_, Apr 15 2006
Row sums of triangle A134842. - _Gary W. Adamson_, Nov 12 2007
G.f.: x/(1-x) = Sum_{n >= 1} a(n)*x^n/(1-x^n)^2. - _Paul D. Hanna_, Aug 16 2008
a(n) = phi(rad(n)) *(-1)^omega(n) = A000010(A007947(n)) *(-1)^A001221(n). - _Enrique Pérez Herrero_, Aug 24 2010
a(n) = Product_{i = 2..n} (1-i)^( (pi(i)-pi(i-1)) * floor( (cos(n*Pi/i))^2 ) ), where pi = A000720, Pi = A000796. - _Wesley Ivan Hurt_, May 24 2013
a(n) = -limit of zeta(s)*(Sum_{d divides n} moebius(d)/exp(d)^(s-1)) as s->1 for n>1. - _Mats Granvik_, Jul 31 2013
a(n) = Sum_{d divides n} mu(d)* rad(d), where rad is A007947. - _Enrique Pérez Herrero_, May 29 2014

Conjecture for n>1: Let n = 2^(A007814(n))*m = 2^(ruler(n))*odd_part(n), where m = A000265(n), then a(n) = (-1)^(m=n)*(0+Sum_{i=1..m and gcd(i,m)=1} (4*min(i,m-i)-m)) = (-1)^(m<n)*(1+Sum_{i=1..m and gcd(i,m)>1} (4*min(i,m-i)-m)). - _I. V. Serov_, May 02 2017
a(1) = 1; for n > 1, a(n) = (1-A020639(n)) * a(A028234(n)), because multiplicative with a(p^e) = (1-p). - _Antti Karttunen_, Nov 28 2017
a(n) = 1 - Sum_{d|n, d > 1} d*a(n/d). - _Ilya Gutkovskiy_, Apr 26 2019

A023916.name: Theta series of A*_4 lattice.
formula: Expansion of f(-x)^5 / f(-x^5) + 5 * x * f(-x^5)^5 / f(-x) in powers of x where f() is a Ramanujan theta function. - _Michael Somos_, Jan 29 2011
G.f. is a period 1 Fourier series which satisfies f(-1 / (5 t)) = 5^(1/2) (t/i)^2 g(t) where q = exp(2*Pi*i*t) and g() is g.f. for A008444. - _Michael Somos_, Jan 29 2011

A023918.name: Theta series of A*_6 lattice.
formula: Expansion of f(-x)^7 / f(-x^7) + 7 * x * f(-x)^3 * f(-x^7)^3 + 7 * x^2 * f(-x^7)^7 / f(-x) in powers of x where f() is a Ramanujan theta function. - _Michael Somos_, Jan 29 2011

A023920.name: Theta series of A*_8 lattice.
formula: E4(9z)+18*eta^12(9z)/eta^4(3z) (E4(9z) term because A*_8 contains E8 as a sublattice). - _Kok Seng Chua_, May 02 2000

A023922.name: Theta series of A*_10 lattice.
formula: G.f.: eta^11(q)/eta(q^11) + 800*q^5*eta^11(q^11)/eta(11) - 9*P11(q)*eta^11(q) + (308/3)*A(q) + (22/3)*B(q), where P11(q) is the g.f. for A213256, A(q) is the g.f. for A065103, B(q) is the g.f. for A065099, and eta is the Dedekind eta function [from Ono]. - _Sean A. Irvine_, Jun 16 2019

A023997.name: Number of block permutations on an n-set.
formula: a(0)=1, a(n) = Sum_{k=1..n} k! * S2(n,k)^2, S2(n,k) are the Stirling numbers of the second kind.

A023998.name: Number of block permutations on an n-set which are uniform, i.e., corresponding blocks have same size.
formula: a(n) = Sum_{k=0..n-1} C(n,k)*C(n-1,k)*a(k) for n>0 with a(0)=1. - _Paul D. Hanna_, Aug 15 2007
G.f.: Sum_{n>=0} a(n)*x^n/n!^2 = exp( Sum_{n>=1} x^n/n!^2 ). [_Paul D. Hanna_, Jan 04 2011; merged from duplicate entry A179119]
Generating function: Let J(z) = sum {n>=0} z^n/n!^2. Then exp(x*(J(z)-1) = sum {n>=0} a(n)*z^n/n!^2 = 1 + z + 3*z^2/2!^2 + 36*z^3/3!^2 + .... - _Peter Bala_, Jul 11 2011

A023999.name: Absolute value of determinant of n X n matrix whose entries are the integers from 1 to n^2 spiraling inward, starting in a corner.

A024000.name: a(n) = 1 - n.
formula: a(n) = Sum_{k=0..n} A094816(n,k)*(-1)^k (alternating row sums of Poisson-Charlier coefficient matrix).
a(n) = 2*a(n-1)-a(n-2) for n>1. - _Wesley Ivan Hurt_, Mar 02 2016
